1
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,960
PREVIOUS EPISODE

2
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:34,120
Hey, you! Wait!

3
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:38,960
Our phones got switched.

4
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:40,560
SATURDAY MARCH 14TH

5
00:02:41,640 --> 00:02:43,640
- Hey.
- Don't explain anything.

6
00:02:43,720 --> 00:02:47,840
The Agriculture Fair is today.
We can use the chaos to move the goods.

7
00:02:47,920 --> 00:02:49,000
Fine.

8
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:51,840
What's your name again?

9
00:02:51,920 --> 00:02:52,880
Poona.

10
00:02:52,960 --> 00:02:57,520
Tonight, go up there and sing the song
you think you sing best.

11
00:02:57,600 --> 00:02:58,920
I'll be listening.

12
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:02,760
If Poona gets to sing, I'm going up too.

13
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:07,440
We only go out when necessary.

14
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:10,520
Under no circumstances
can the people here know who we are.

15
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:14,640
Pleaw Paknampho has come up
to take a job in this area.

16
00:03:14,720 --> 00:03:16,280
Pleaw Paknampho?

17
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:23,520
- Stop!
- Stop here.

18
00:03:26,720 --> 00:03:27,760
Let us search the car.

19
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:29,160
On what charge?

20
00:03:29,760 --> 00:03:31,240
Any illegal items.

21
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:41,200
You're under arrest

22
00:03:42,520 --> 00:03:45,160
for possession of military-grade weapons.
Get out of the car!

23
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:48,200
Arrest me.

24
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:51,520
Just see if you can keep up. Go!

25
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:55,320
Hey! Get the car!

26
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:14,600
KHOK TA YU AGRICULTURE FAIR

27
00:04:51,080 --> 00:04:54,880
A big thank you to all our beloved fans

28
00:04:54,960 --> 00:04:59,520
for supporting the Mueangphrai Band

29
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:02,520
and for being here tonight. Tonight,

30
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:07,080
you're about to meet a stunning singer
with a voice as smooth as beer foam.

31
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:12,840
Maria, Village Head Prueng's daughter,
performing "Motorbike in a Short Skirt".

32
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:53,640
Hear that applause, Poona?

33
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:00,760
Try to be like me.

34
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:06,320
I got a 20 baht tip.
Try to be like me, Poona.

35
00:06:06,400 --> 00:06:10,080
I danced so hard, my pants split open.
Try to be like me, Poona.

36
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:13,080
Boo.

37
00:06:15,080 --> 00:06:17,720
You want it, don't you? Too bad.

38
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:20,160
Twenty baht!

39
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:25,920
Poona, it's your turn. Get ready.
Come on, you got this.

40
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:40,480
KHOK TA YU AGRICULTURE FAIR

41
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:09,080
KHOK TA YU AGRICULTURE FAIR

42
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:20,920
She's pretty good.

43
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:35,920
Poona deserves to be a singer.

44
00:07:38,840 --> 00:07:41,400
A gem like this deserves to be polished.

45
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:44,000
Yes.

46
00:07:45,960 --> 00:07:48,560
The apple doesn't fall far from the tree.

47
00:07:50,520 --> 00:07:52,440
The apple doesn't fall far from the tree?

48
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:56,640
You know Poona?

49
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:08,680
Boss. Boss.

50
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:11,680
Boss! Boss.

51
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:13,600
Look at you.

52
00:08:15,320 --> 00:08:17,920
What do you think, Boss?

53
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:18,960
Who is she, Chang?

54
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:22,600
A new singer, Boss.
I heard she's from Nern Samran.

55
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,480
She asked to sing tonight.

56
00:08:35,480 --> 00:08:38,840
Wow, the crowd's really applauding Poona.

57
00:08:38,919 --> 00:08:41,320
KHOK TA YU AGRICULTURE FAIR

58
00:08:41,400 --> 00:08:42,799
They're all paid plants.

59
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:45,920
That's not what paid plants look like.
They'd look like this.

60
00:08:48,280 --> 00:08:49,760
Then why don't we have paid plants?

61
00:08:49,840 --> 00:08:52,400
Why would we need them? We have fans.

62
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:55,240
Real fans are better.
Paid plants have to be hired.

63
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:57,640
Don't flatter me.

64
00:08:58,640 --> 00:09:00,920
Then where would Poona
get the money to hire them?!

65
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:03,160
Well…

66
00:09:04,040 --> 00:09:05,280
Hello.

67
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:07,440
Hello there.

68
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:10,480
What's the singer's name?

69
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:14,720
Her name is Maria.
She's Village Head Prueng's daughter.

70
00:09:14,800 --> 00:09:16,600
- Oh, Maria.
- That's right.

71
00:09:16,680 --> 00:09:19,560
You sing really well.
So I'd like to give you a reward.

72
00:09:21,640 --> 00:09:22,720
Wow.

73
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:26,720
See, Miss Maria? He's one of your fans.

74
00:09:34,280 --> 00:09:36,080
- Hello.
- Hello.

75
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:38,400
Did you like my song?

76
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:45,040
Yes, you sing beautifully.

77
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:47,600
So I'd like to give you
a little reward. Here.

78
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:48,960
Poona! Poona!

79
00:10:49,040 --> 00:10:50,920
- Chang.
- Yes?

80
00:10:51,440 --> 00:10:53,440
She sings really beautifully, doesn't she?

81
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:55,560
Well, and more importantly,

82
00:10:56,160 --> 00:10:58,320
she's beautiful and charming too.

83
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:06,000
Poona! Poona!

84
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:09,960
Excuse me, miss.

85
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:13,240
You sang beautifully.

86
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:16,000
I have a little reward for you.

87
00:11:19,920 --> 00:11:21,200
Consider this my prize for you.

88
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:30,800
Thank you.

89
00:11:42,640 --> 00:11:44,360
What kind of signal is that?

90
00:11:46,160 --> 00:11:48,080
They're definitely in cahoots.

91
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:51,120
KHOK TA YU AGRICULTURE FAIR

92
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:57,000
Chit just went backstage
to give the singer an award.

93
00:11:58,160 --> 00:11:59,600
Seems like a signal.

94
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:08,640
Alright then,

95
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:11,840
I'll get going now. See you next time.

96
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:14,520
Okay. Thank you so much.

97
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:18,240
Don't forget to follow our YouTube
channel, Village Head Prik Music.

98
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:19,560
Village Head Prueng Music!

99
00:12:19,640 --> 00:12:21,120
Just kidding.

100
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:22,160
Right, that's funny.

101
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:24,880
- Come tip us again.
- Sure.

102
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:27,080
- See you next time.
- See you.

103
00:12:27,160 --> 00:12:28,280
Bye.

104
00:12:28,360 --> 00:12:31,240
See you.

105
00:12:32,320 --> 00:12:33,840
Two thousand baht.

106
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:36,720
I'm so happy.

107
00:12:37,760 --> 00:12:40,400
See? We have our own fans too.

108
00:12:41,320 --> 00:12:44,720
There are cops at the fair.
So I had Tod hide the goods first.

109
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:46,760
We can't make the drop yet.

110
00:12:47,280 --> 00:12:50,200
Good. Then don't hand over the goods yet.

111
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:53,600
If we get busted,
this turns into a major problem.

112
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:55,320
Yes, Boss.

113
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:12,000
Oh my!

114
00:13:12,080 --> 00:13:15,720
Hundreds and even thousand-baht bills?
Still not enough to beat us.

115
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:17,920
We got 2,020.

116
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:20,320
Exactly. We got more than you.

117
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:22,720
She got more than us. Look!

118
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:25,840
You only got more because you hired them.

119
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:28,360
I can't afford to hire anyone.

120
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:30,960
And I'm not trying
to compete with anyone either.

121
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:35,200
Now that you got more tips,
you pretend you're not competing.

122
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:40,720
Where are my clothes?

123
00:13:41,360 --> 00:13:42,520
Huh?

124
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:45,520
- They were hanging right here just now.
- Exactly.

125
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:46,480
What?

126
00:13:49,320 --> 00:13:50,760
Where did they go?

127
00:13:51,720 --> 00:13:52,640
Poona!

128
00:13:53,520 --> 00:13:56,680
It has to be you.
You hid them on purpose, didn't you?

129
00:13:57,280 --> 00:14:01,080
I didn't. My clothes are missing too.

130
00:14:01,640 --> 00:14:03,320
Where did they go?

131
00:14:04,160 --> 00:14:07,080
Sophie, Joey, go check the dancers' area.
See if they're there.

132
00:14:07,160 --> 00:14:08,760
- Okay.
- Yeah, let's go.

133
00:14:12,760 --> 00:14:14,720
Where did they go?

134
00:14:18,760 --> 00:14:20,920
They look like the ones moving the drugs.

135
00:14:26,280 --> 00:14:27,480
Look at them.

136
00:14:28,120 --> 00:14:30,440
They're searching everywhere
for the hidden stash.

137
00:14:34,360 --> 00:14:35,200
KHOK TA YU AGRICULTURE FAIR

138
00:14:35,280 --> 00:14:38,000
Hey, where do you think you're going?

139
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:40,720
Boss Noo sent me to pick up the goods.

140
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:43,960
Hold on. Now's not a good time.

141
00:14:44,960 --> 00:14:46,040
Trying to pull something?

142
00:14:47,520 --> 00:14:51,000
Don't you get it?
I said we're not making the drop yet.

143
00:14:51,080 --> 00:14:52,520
You sure about that?

144
00:14:54,840 --> 00:14:56,640
Chit, the cops are here.

145
00:14:58,640 --> 00:15:02,040
The same old trick.
You think I'd fall for that?

146
00:15:02,120 --> 00:15:03,800
I'm getting the goods today,
no matter what.

147
00:15:03,880 --> 00:15:07,240
You want the goods?
Then go get them from the cops.

148
00:15:17,880 --> 00:15:20,120
Chit, what do we do?

149
00:15:22,960 --> 00:15:25,080
- You hid the goods already, right?
- Don't worry.

150
00:15:34,440 --> 00:15:37,440
Police. We need to conduct a search.

151
00:15:39,240 --> 00:15:40,480
Hello, Officer.

152
00:15:41,120 --> 00:15:42,920
May I ask what you're looking for?

153
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:44,000
Drugs.

154
00:15:44,080 --> 00:15:45,360
Drugs?

155
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:48,040
You got any? Do you?

156
00:15:48,120 --> 00:15:49,000
No.

157
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:51,200
Hands up.

158
00:15:51,280 --> 00:15:53,560
Easy, Officer.

159
00:15:58,280 --> 00:16:01,720
Took the money, but no delivery.

160
00:16:02,080 --> 00:16:02,920
Find anything?

161
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:04,920
Nothing.

162
00:16:05,680 --> 00:16:06,600
Let's go.

163
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:11,240
Excuse us.

164
00:16:28,680 --> 00:16:29,560
What's this bag?

165
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:41,800
What is it, Miss Maria?

166
00:16:41,880 --> 00:16:42,800
What did Poona do?

167
00:16:42,880 --> 00:16:44,640
What is it, Maria? Don't mess around.

168
00:16:54,120 --> 00:16:55,720
This looks like drugs.

169
00:16:58,880 --> 00:17:03,800
Tod, Wong, head back
and help our men watch the stash.

170
00:17:04,319 --> 00:17:06,359
The cops don't seem willing
to let this go.

171
00:17:06,440 --> 00:17:09,079
Right. If anyone takes the drugs,
we'll know who to track down.

172
00:17:09,680 --> 00:17:13,200
Good. Then you and Wong go back
and watch the stash.

173
00:17:13,280 --> 00:17:14,119
Got it.

174
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:21,240
This way!

175
00:17:21,319 --> 00:17:24,040
- Everyone, get out of here first!
- Right!

176
00:17:26,880 --> 00:17:30,240
Hurry!

177
00:17:31,920 --> 00:17:33,320
They're getting away, Manat. Move!

178
00:17:35,480 --> 00:17:38,640
Oh no, I'm not involved in this!

179
00:17:39,520 --> 00:17:41,680
This is so scary!

180
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:48,160
- What's going on?
- Let go!

181
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:51,720
Let go! I said let go!

182
00:17:51,800 --> 00:17:53,520
Let go of her!

183
00:18:00,800 --> 00:18:03,160
- Hurry!
- Manat, after them!

184
00:18:03,240 --> 00:18:04,480
Ouch!

185
00:18:18,560 --> 00:18:19,640
Who's Chit's group having trouble with?

186
00:18:19,720 --> 00:18:21,960
The other side
looks like Pleaw Paknampho, sir.

187
00:18:23,080 --> 00:18:25,040
You two, split up
and move around behind them.

188
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:26,320
Yes, sir.

189
00:18:28,040 --> 00:18:29,800
Go! Get backstage and hide. Hurry!

190
00:18:29,880 --> 00:18:30,720
What's going on?

191
00:18:33,880 --> 00:18:36,040
Hide in there first. Go!

192
00:18:42,640 --> 00:18:45,040
- How is it? Did you find them?
- They went that way.

193
00:19:08,760 --> 00:19:11,000
What are you doing? Help, thief!

194
00:19:11,080 --> 00:19:12,800
Hey! What are you doing in here? Thieves?

195
00:19:12,880 --> 00:19:14,400
- Get out right now!
- Thief!

196
00:19:14,480 --> 00:19:15,880
No, ma'am. We're looking for someone.

197
00:19:15,960 --> 00:19:18,120
- Looking for what?
- Don't make excuses. Get out!

198
00:19:18,200 --> 00:19:21,680
Get out of here right now.
You're too handsome to be thieves.

199
00:19:21,760 --> 00:19:22,880
Get out!

200
00:19:22,960 --> 00:19:24,960
- Get out!
- Got it.

201
00:19:25,040 --> 00:19:26,840
Alright, we're going.

202
00:19:26,920 --> 00:19:28,040
Get out of here!

203
00:19:28,120 --> 00:19:30,480
- With faces like that, why do this?
- Right.

204
00:19:46,960 --> 00:19:49,880
Poona, you hid me in that tent,
and we almost got caught.

205
00:19:50,560 --> 00:19:52,960
But it got us out safely, didn't it?
Stop complaining.

206
00:19:53,880 --> 00:19:55,480
Come on, hurry!

207
00:19:57,600 --> 00:19:58,880
- Which way?
- Gotcha!

208
00:19:58,960 --> 00:19:59,840
Oh no!

209
00:20:01,560 --> 00:20:03,040
Thought you'd get away?

210
00:20:03,120 --> 00:20:04,160
So, here you are.

211
00:20:04,760 --> 00:20:06,120
- Come here.
- Come here.

212
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:07,440
Idiot! Let go!

213
00:20:07,520 --> 00:20:09,360
- Just come quietly.
- Who are you? Let go!

214
00:20:09,440 --> 00:20:10,400
Stop struggling.

215
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:12,040
Come on, stop!

216
00:20:24,760 --> 00:20:25,920
Bomb!

217
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:27,200
We should get to the car.

218
00:20:28,160 --> 00:20:29,120
Sorn, watch out!

219
00:20:55,480 --> 00:20:56,920
KHOK TA YU AGRICULTURE FAIR

220
00:21:01,280 --> 00:21:03,160
- What about those two women?
- They got away.

221
00:21:04,120 --> 00:21:05,480
Hey, you alright?

222
00:21:05,560 --> 00:21:07,560
I'm okay. You?

223
00:21:07,640 --> 00:21:08,800
I'm good.

224
00:21:10,320 --> 00:21:11,840
Come on, let's go after them.

225
00:21:19,240 --> 00:21:20,760
We lost them, Pleaw.

226
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:23,560
Hunt them down and find them.

227
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:29,880
- Where's the car key?
- Don't know. Still looking.

228
00:21:29,960 --> 00:21:30,800
Look properly.

229
00:21:30,880 --> 00:21:32,360
Check again.

230
00:21:32,440 --> 00:21:34,480
You really think you can get away from me?

231
00:21:41,160 --> 00:21:42,440
Leave the car. Run for it.

232
00:21:42,520 --> 00:21:43,360
- Go!
- Let's go!

233
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:48,880
Stop! Police!

234
00:21:50,240 --> 00:21:51,280
Move!

235
00:21:53,320 --> 00:21:54,200
After them!

236
00:21:55,880 --> 00:21:56,760
Hey, stop!

237
00:22:01,280 --> 00:22:02,280
Put the gun down.

238
00:22:04,960 --> 00:22:05,920
Slowly.

239
00:22:10,160 --> 00:22:12,560
Hands behind your back. Now!

240
00:22:22,600 --> 00:22:23,440
After them!

241
00:22:23,520 --> 00:22:24,760
We made it out safe.

242
00:22:26,440 --> 00:22:30,160
- No, please! I'm scared!
- Stop right there.

243
00:22:30,680 --> 00:22:34,080
Hey! Pleaw's taken Paula
and that woman hostage.

244
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:36,280
Take whatever you want.
They're all fake anyway!

245
00:22:36,360 --> 00:22:37,960
- They're fake!
- Shut up!

246
00:22:39,040 --> 00:22:39,920
What do we do, Chaiya?

247
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:43,520
Forget those two troublemakers for now.
We help them first.

248
00:22:44,560 --> 00:22:45,400
Go!

249
00:22:46,120 --> 00:22:47,320
Don't hurt the women.

250
00:22:47,400 --> 00:22:49,400
Back off, or I shoot.

251
00:22:49,480 --> 00:22:50,760
Oh no! Take it easy!

252
00:22:52,120 --> 00:22:53,720
Officer.

253
00:22:54,320 --> 00:22:57,080
Please back off first. Don't shoot.
I'm begging you.

254
00:22:57,160 --> 00:23:00,360
Wait, are you on their side?

255
00:23:00,440 --> 00:23:03,200
Don't talk. Right now,
we need to survive first.

256
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:06,040
Back off. Please back off.

257
00:23:06,120 --> 00:23:08,600
Oh my, gun in front, gun in back!

258
00:23:14,720 --> 00:23:16,840
This feels so warm and comforting.

259
00:23:17,920 --> 00:23:19,400
Take care of yourself, ma'am.

260
00:23:26,400 --> 00:23:27,920
So cool!

261
00:23:31,440 --> 00:23:33,560
Heaven really let me witness this.

262
00:23:33,640 --> 00:23:35,880
I just want to wipe his sweat.
Oh, so handsome.

263
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:47,040
Stop right now!

264
00:23:52,720 --> 00:23:53,800
- On your knees.
- Hey!

265
00:23:53,880 --> 00:23:56,160
- On your knees.
- Don't resist.

266
00:23:56,240 --> 00:23:58,840
- What is this?
- I haven't done anything, Officer.

267
00:23:58,920 --> 00:23:59,800
Shut up.

268
00:23:59,880 --> 00:24:02,320
Captain, you should be the one to shut up!
Oh my goodness!

269
00:24:02,400 --> 00:24:06,040
Put the gun away right now!
You must've had such a fright.

270
00:24:06,120 --> 00:24:07,520
Auntie!

271
00:24:08,360 --> 00:24:09,680
Call me ma'am!

272
00:24:10,440 --> 00:24:11,280
Ma'am it is.

273
00:24:11,880 --> 00:24:16,360
Alright, Officer,
these two are not the bad guys.

274
00:24:16,440 --> 00:24:19,240
They're good men. They came to help us.

275
00:24:19,320 --> 00:24:21,960
It's true. I can be a witness.

276
00:24:22,040 --> 00:24:25,920
The two of us were taken hostage,
and these two came to save us.

277
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:28,280
These two are good citizens, Captain.

278
00:24:29,120 --> 00:24:30,800
Put that gun away already.

279
00:24:32,560 --> 00:24:34,560
Oh dear.

280
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:38,240
You must've had such a fright, didn't you?

281
00:24:39,560 --> 00:24:43,360
In that case, we owe you an apology
for misunderstanding you.

282
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:48,240
It's alright. If there's
nothing else, we'll be going.

283
00:24:51,040 --> 00:24:51,880
Wait. Hold on.

284
00:25:00,440 --> 00:25:01,960
Are either of you hurt anywhere?

285
00:25:02,040 --> 00:25:04,280
Do you want to get that checked first?
I can take you.

286
00:25:04,360 --> 00:25:07,080
Just a few bruises, that's all.

287
00:25:07,160 --> 00:25:09,400
Thank you very much, Captain.
We'll be going now.

288
00:25:10,040 --> 00:25:12,880
Thank you too. Bye!

289
00:25:12,960 --> 00:25:14,480
Why are they in such a hurry?

290
00:25:14,560 --> 00:25:19,520
Oh, Officer, after a situation like this,
anyone would rush home.

291
00:25:19,600 --> 00:25:21,200
Who'd stay here and risk getting shot?

292
00:25:21,840 --> 00:25:23,240
Honestly, you just don't get it.

293
00:25:24,040 --> 00:25:25,960
Do you know those two?

294
00:25:26,040 --> 00:25:29,320
Of course. They're renting
a house from me.

295
00:25:29,400 --> 00:25:33,160
They're YouTubers from Bangkok.
Premium stuff, very rare items.

296
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:36,560
I should go after them. Wait for me!

297
00:25:36,640 --> 00:25:39,840
How are you going? Let me come too!

298
00:25:43,200 --> 00:25:45,600
- Are you alright, Boss?
- I'm fine.

299
00:25:45,680 --> 00:25:48,600
I think we should leave.
This place isn't safe anymore. Let's go.

300
00:25:48,680 --> 00:25:51,240
Hey! Someone's hurt over here.
Can you help?

301
00:25:52,440 --> 00:25:54,680
Let's go. Time to leave.

302
00:25:54,760 --> 00:25:56,280
Come on, Chang! Let's head back.

303
00:25:57,120 --> 00:25:58,040
Hey, Chang!

304
00:25:58,760 --> 00:26:00,760
Isn't that the singer from the stage?

305
00:26:03,920 --> 00:26:06,120
Hey, Chang, what do we do?

306
00:26:07,240 --> 00:26:10,280
If we don't help,
the villagers will roast us, Mr. Sornrak.

307
00:26:15,080 --> 00:26:17,480
- Camera. Get the camera rolling!
- Okay.

308
00:26:17,560 --> 00:26:19,320
- Okay, ready.
- Start recording.

309
00:26:19,400 --> 00:26:20,280
Alright, follow me.

310
00:26:21,840 --> 00:26:25,640
Uncle, are you alright?
Take the injured person to the car.

311
00:26:26,360 --> 00:26:29,680
I'll help this one myself.
You okay? Get in that car.

312
00:26:36,400 --> 00:26:37,760
Miss.

313
00:26:39,760 --> 00:26:40,640
Are you alright?

314
00:26:42,320 --> 00:26:44,400
I'm here to help. Miss.

315
00:26:47,800 --> 00:26:49,120
Excuse me. Don't be afraid.

316
00:26:50,720 --> 00:26:53,760
<i>I'm here to help you. Let's go.</i>

317
00:26:56,480 --> 00:26:59,920
Don't be scared. I've got you.

318
00:27:07,640 --> 00:27:09,640
- Wait, that's Poona!
- What?

319
00:27:12,120 --> 00:27:14,040
Are you alright?

320
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:20,120
I'm okay. I'm just winded,
and there's only a little bleeding.

321
00:27:20,200 --> 00:27:23,760
Hurry, take her to the hospital.

322
00:27:23,840 --> 00:27:26,760
No, please. I don't want
to go to the hospital.

323
00:27:28,520 --> 00:27:32,800
If I go, Uncle will beat me to death.

324
00:27:33,320 --> 00:27:34,360
Uncle?

325
00:27:35,840 --> 00:27:39,600
I don't want to go to the hospital.
I can get home by myself, really.

326
00:27:39,680 --> 00:27:42,720
How can you? You're hurt this badly.
No matter what, you have to go.

327
00:27:48,360 --> 00:27:49,560
My dear!

328
00:27:52,960 --> 00:27:54,240
Please don't be hurt.

329
00:28:05,560 --> 00:28:09,760
UNCLE THARIN

330
00:28:46,320 --> 00:28:47,600
Take it slow.

331
00:28:55,520 --> 00:28:59,760
You're not badly hurt.
Looks like shrapnel knocked you out.

332
00:29:02,880 --> 00:29:03,720
Thank you.

333
00:29:04,560 --> 00:29:07,840
Your phone rang earlier,
but I didn't answer it.

334
00:29:08,560 --> 00:29:10,240
They called several times.

335
00:29:14,480 --> 00:29:15,320
Oh no.

336
00:29:18,200 --> 00:29:19,760
What are your parents' names?

337
00:29:20,560 --> 00:29:24,280
Once you're feeling better,
I'll take you home.

338
00:29:25,920 --> 00:29:27,880
My father's name is Phupha.

339
00:29:31,960 --> 00:29:35,320
Phupha, the famous singer back then?

340
00:29:37,800 --> 00:29:38,800
Yes.

341
00:29:49,880 --> 00:29:54,160
My father's name is Phupha Thararin.
He used to be a singer.

342
00:29:56,320 --> 00:29:58,200
But he passed away.

343
00:30:01,160 --> 00:30:04,280
Right now, I live with Uncle Tharin,
my father's younger brother.

344
00:30:05,720 --> 00:30:07,720
Do you know my father too?

345
00:30:18,120 --> 00:30:20,120
Who wouldn't know your father?

346
00:30:25,920 --> 00:30:29,560
Poona, have something to eat first,

347
00:30:30,160 --> 00:30:31,400
so you can rest.

348
00:30:33,280 --> 00:30:35,360
Stay here tonight.

349
00:30:38,080 --> 00:30:39,360
But…

350
00:30:41,480 --> 00:30:45,160
If I go back tomorrow,
Uncle Tharin will definitely beat me.

351
00:30:45,240 --> 00:30:47,840
But I think it's dangerous outside.

352
00:30:47,920 --> 00:30:50,040
There are explosions everywhere.
No one knows what's going on.

353
00:30:50,120 --> 00:30:53,640
Stay here tonight.
It's safer inside the house.

354
00:30:56,400 --> 00:30:57,840
It's alright.

355
00:30:59,320 --> 00:31:01,360
I'll take you home myself tomorrow.

356
00:31:21,080 --> 00:31:23,320
Is Poona the child you told me about?

357
00:31:24,160 --> 00:31:28,440
Yes, she is…

358
00:31:31,280 --> 00:31:33,400
If you go to Poona's house,

359
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:35,280
what are you going to do?

360
00:31:36,240 --> 00:31:40,360
Phupha had a twin brother named Tharin.

361
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:44,120
But the one who died that day,

362
00:31:45,360 --> 00:31:48,200
I still can't believe it was Phupha.

363
00:31:58,440 --> 00:31:59,520
Phupha.

364
00:32:01,200 --> 00:32:04,240
Phupha, wake up.

365
00:32:04,320 --> 00:32:07,040
Phupha. Phupha!

366
00:32:10,320 --> 00:32:12,120
Phupha, wake up.

367
00:32:24,760 --> 00:32:25,760
Phupha…

368
00:32:29,800 --> 00:32:31,000
Namthip.

369
00:32:31,640 --> 00:32:35,640
Namthip, you're not dead, are you?

370
00:32:36,240 --> 00:32:40,920
You have to go back to Poona.
You have to go back to your daughter.

371
00:32:46,280 --> 00:32:47,680
Don't die yet, please.

372
00:33:01,240 --> 00:33:02,760
Hey, finish it.

373
00:33:39,320 --> 00:33:41,000
Phupha!

374
00:33:42,880 --> 00:33:45,080
Wait! If Phupha is still alive,

375
00:33:45,160 --> 00:33:47,400
that means they killed the wrong person.

376
00:33:50,400 --> 00:33:55,320
If I get to meet Poona's uncle tomorrow,
I'll know for sure

377
00:33:56,080 --> 00:33:57,800
whether they killed the wrong person.

378
00:34:00,240 --> 00:34:01,280
I think

379
00:34:02,360 --> 00:34:03,960
it was fate

380
00:34:04,560 --> 00:34:06,680
that brought me to Poona.

381
00:34:07,960 --> 00:34:11,679
Maybe my chance for revenge

382
00:34:12,639 --> 00:34:14,560
has finally come.

383
00:34:22,360 --> 00:34:25,159
KHOK TA YU AGRICULTURE FAIR

384
00:34:31,560 --> 00:34:32,440
How's it going, Au?

385
00:34:33,520 --> 00:34:34,840
You know who I am, Captain.

386
00:34:37,679 --> 00:34:38,520
Here.

387
00:34:39,800 --> 00:34:40,639
Amazing, Au.

388
00:34:43,960 --> 00:34:47,000
Collect everything. It could
be evidence from the scene.

389
00:34:47,880 --> 00:34:52,000
Understood. I'll check over there too,
in case I find anything else.

390
00:34:57,920 --> 00:35:00,880
I feel bad for the villagers.
They didn't even break even last night.

391
00:35:00,960 --> 00:35:02,000
Then they had to run from an explosion.

392
00:35:04,120 --> 00:35:06,880
It's because of those damned drug dealers.

393
00:35:07,400 --> 00:35:11,360
I swear I'll put every last one of them
behind bars.

394
00:35:14,200 --> 00:35:18,240
There were several explosions last night.
Quite a few people got hurt too.

395
00:35:18,320 --> 00:35:20,600
Try checking the hospital records.

396
00:35:21,200 --> 00:35:24,520
I already asked at the hospital.
My niece's name isn't there.

397
00:35:26,560 --> 00:35:29,840
I don't know where she's gone.
She hasn't contacted me either.

398
00:35:29,920 --> 00:35:31,520
Could she be at her boyfriend's place?

399
00:35:33,760 --> 00:35:35,520
My niece doesn't have a boyfriend.

400
00:35:35,600 --> 00:35:37,280
Come on. Kids these days,

401
00:35:37,360 --> 00:35:39,840
a day or two together,
and they're already sleeping together.

402
00:35:42,840 --> 00:35:44,400
My niece is not that kind of girl!

403
00:35:44,480 --> 00:35:46,080
- Oh.
- Well.

404
00:35:51,240 --> 00:35:53,600
Chaiya!

405
00:35:54,440 --> 00:35:56,920
Oh my, the ground is so wet.

406
00:35:57,000 --> 00:35:58,240
So hard for a beauty to walk.

407
00:35:59,240 --> 00:36:00,200
It's Paula.

408
00:36:00,280 --> 00:36:04,360
Of course, it's me. How do I look today?

409
00:36:04,440 --> 00:36:07,560
Beautiful, right?

410
00:36:07,640 --> 00:36:08,600
Very lovely.

411
00:36:09,840 --> 00:36:11,720
Lovely, huh? But do you love me?

412
00:36:14,080 --> 00:36:16,840
Well, I'm still enjoying the single life.

413
00:36:18,160 --> 00:36:21,120
Oh my! We're on the same wavelength.

414
00:36:21,200 --> 00:36:25,960
I've always loved being single too.
I never looked at anyone.

415
00:36:26,040 --> 00:36:27,720
But the moment I met you, Chaiya,

416
00:36:27,800 --> 00:36:30,720
I haven't wanted to look at anyone else.

417
00:36:30,800 --> 00:36:32,400
Seriously.

418
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:35,560
Anyway, what are you doing here?

419
00:36:35,640 --> 00:36:39,680
There was a shooting last night,
so I came to check for damage.

420
00:36:41,160 --> 00:36:44,000
Just thinking about last night
still gives me chills.

421
00:36:44,880 --> 00:36:47,360
I'm getting some content
for our YouTube channel.

422
00:36:48,160 --> 00:36:51,880
Oh, YouTube? I already follow
your channel, Chaiya.

423
00:36:51,960 --> 00:36:53,160
That's very sweet of you.

424
00:36:53,680 --> 00:36:57,240
KHOK TA YU AGRICULTURE FAIR

425
00:36:58,760 --> 00:37:00,160
Auntie, have you seen Poona?

426
00:37:00,240 --> 00:37:03,160
Okay? So handsome.

427
00:37:03,240 --> 00:37:04,680
Have you seen Poona?

428
00:37:07,120 --> 00:37:08,360
You've got dimples too.

429
00:37:08,440 --> 00:37:10,520
- Paula.
- Yes?

430
00:37:10,600 --> 00:37:11,840
Have you seen Poona?

431
00:37:12,480 --> 00:37:13,320
No, I haven't.

432
00:37:20,120 --> 00:37:21,120
I don't know where she's gone.

433
00:37:23,360 --> 00:37:25,240
- Excuse me, then.
- Alright.

434
00:37:28,080 --> 00:37:29,080
Poona?

435
00:37:30,000 --> 00:37:32,480
The one who sang
on stage last night, right?

436
00:37:32,560 --> 00:37:33,600
Yes.

437
00:37:34,240 --> 00:37:36,160
Was that her father just now?

438
00:37:36,840 --> 00:37:38,760
No, that was her uncle.

439
00:37:40,400 --> 00:37:44,120
Do you want to know about Poona?
I can tell you everything.

440
00:37:44,200 --> 00:37:47,080
I know all the details.
Since I'm already telling the story,

441
00:37:47,160 --> 00:37:51,080
anyone who wants to know about Poona,
come right here.

442
00:37:51,160 --> 00:37:52,200
Ask me anything.

443
00:37:52,280 --> 00:37:56,240
I heard her parents had a scandal.
Did they die because of an affair?

444
00:37:56,320 --> 00:37:59,160
You really know your stuff. It's all true.

445
00:38:00,720 --> 00:38:04,600
Listen, everyone. Poona's father
was a singer named Phupha.

446
00:38:05,200 --> 00:38:08,440
Her mother was Namthip.
Then Phupha ended up

447
00:38:08,520 --> 00:38:11,200
having an affair
with another singer named Onanong.

448
00:38:11,280 --> 00:38:13,160
That family fell apart. In the end,

449
00:38:13,240 --> 00:38:16,080
they killed each other.
Jealousy, you know.

450
00:38:16,600 --> 00:38:21,320
So shameless. That's disgusting.

451
00:38:23,240 --> 00:38:24,800
- Ma'am.
- Yes?

452
00:38:24,880 --> 00:38:27,280
You shouldn't say things like that
without evidence.

453
00:38:27,960 --> 00:38:31,720
It was in almost
every newspaper back then.

454
00:38:31,800 --> 00:38:33,080
But the dead are being defamed.

455
00:38:34,800 --> 00:38:36,280
And they have no right
to defend themselves.

456
00:38:37,520 --> 00:38:42,920
Next time, if you have no proof,
don't say things that ruin someone's name.

457
00:38:43,000 --> 00:38:44,360
They could sue you.

458
00:38:44,440 --> 00:38:47,120
Oh my! Lips zipped.

459
00:38:47,200 --> 00:38:49,920
From now on, I'll believe
every word you say, Chaiya.

460
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:52,600
I won't say anything like this again.

461
00:38:53,200 --> 00:38:57,640
You all dragged me into gossiping,
and now a handsome man scolds me for it.

462
00:38:57,720 --> 00:39:00,720
Ugh! What a mood killer.

463
00:39:00,800 --> 00:39:04,960
Last night, I saw Poona go up
and sing on stage at the fair.

464
00:39:06,400 --> 00:39:10,200
She sang "Waiting for Him to Forget",
by Onanong Wongwichian.

465
00:39:10,280 --> 00:39:12,200
She sang it beautifully.

466
00:39:12,960 --> 00:39:15,920
When the explosion happened,
we all ran for our lives.

467
00:39:16,000 --> 00:39:19,680
Sorry, I really don't know where she went.

468
00:39:20,680 --> 00:39:26,240
I checked with the rescue foundation.
No one died. Only some were injured.

469
00:39:28,480 --> 00:39:32,160
I'm really worried about her.
I don't know why she hasn't contacted me.

470
00:39:32,240 --> 00:39:34,880
Have you gone to the police yet,
Uncle Tharin?

471
00:39:34,960 --> 00:39:37,520
I have, but it didn't get us anywhere.

472
00:39:37,600 --> 00:39:39,000
To be honest, Tharin,

473
00:39:39,760 --> 00:39:43,200
the reason she hasn't contacted you
is because you're too strict.

474
00:39:43,800 --> 00:39:48,280
She's grown up now.
She has no friends, no one to talk to.

475
00:39:48,360 --> 00:39:51,760
She's too afraid to tell you anything.
Especially after what happened,

476
00:39:51,840 --> 00:39:53,840
do you think she'd dare call and tell you?

477
00:39:58,120 --> 00:40:02,080
Maybe you're right. I'll think it over.

478
00:40:03,640 --> 00:40:04,600
I'll be going now, Sroi.

479
00:40:04,680 --> 00:40:05,520
Alright.

480
00:40:07,960 --> 00:40:11,000
If Poona wants to be a singer,
then let her be one, Uncle.

481
00:40:11,080 --> 00:40:14,840
She really has talent.
I want to see her become a singer.

482
00:40:30,960 --> 00:40:32,440
It's already in the news.

483
00:40:32,960 --> 00:40:36,880
Maria is in the hospital now.
Sornrak was the one who saved her.

484
00:40:37,480 --> 00:40:39,000
He's a hero now.

485
00:40:40,520 --> 00:40:41,720
Any news about Poona?

486
00:40:41,800 --> 00:40:42,640
Not yet.

487
00:40:44,040 --> 00:40:45,000
Where could she have gone?

488
00:40:45,080 --> 00:40:48,360
Pretty girls like them shouldn't
have been involved with drug dealers.

489
00:40:48,440 --> 00:40:50,880
- Exactly.
- Exactly?

490
00:40:51,520 --> 00:40:52,720
Exactly what?

491
00:40:53,240 --> 00:40:54,880
They're pretty, exactly what you said.

492
00:40:55,400 --> 00:40:59,160
Especially Maria,
she's beautiful, fair-skinned,

493
00:40:59,800 --> 00:41:03,800
and has such a sweet voice.
Totally my type.

494
00:41:05,440 --> 00:41:07,960
Damn it, all you think about is girls.

495
00:41:08,040 --> 00:41:09,280
Did you forget you could die?

496
00:41:09,360 --> 00:41:10,800
You're right.

497
00:41:11,640 --> 00:41:16,680
I think last night's bombing
was Pleaw Paknampho's people.

498
00:41:18,960 --> 00:41:20,560
Things are this brutal here.

499
00:41:21,200 --> 00:41:23,520
It means the law
is already in the hands of criminals.

500
00:41:35,480 --> 00:41:38,280
Hey, Manat, look over there.

501
00:41:42,240 --> 00:41:43,440
Those are Pleaw's men.

502
00:41:59,280 --> 00:42:03,600
AUNT TAEW PAPAYA SALAD

503
00:42:07,640 --> 00:42:09,280
Mind if we have a word, brother?

504
00:42:11,520 --> 00:42:12,600
What do you want?

505
00:42:12,680 --> 00:42:15,280
Just want to ask you a few questions.

506
00:42:15,880 --> 00:42:18,920
Questions? If you've got questions…

507
00:42:24,360 --> 00:42:25,880
then ask my gun.

508
00:42:43,440 --> 00:42:45,120
I haven't even sold anything yet!

509
00:42:45,760 --> 00:42:47,640
Hey!

510
00:42:55,320 --> 00:42:56,200
Hurry.

511
00:42:59,480 --> 00:43:02,040
If you'd answered him,
you wouldn't be hurt now.

512
00:43:05,840 --> 00:43:06,880
Hey, Pleaw!

513
00:43:11,080 --> 00:43:11,920
Hey, move!

514
00:43:57,520 --> 00:43:59,680
Hey, Manat. Run!

515
00:44:31,040 --> 00:44:32,920
These two are way too skilled
for ordinary people.

516
00:44:34,280 --> 00:44:36,600
Could they be police informants?

517
00:44:40,960 --> 00:44:42,000
Hello, Chit.

518
00:44:43,280 --> 00:44:47,320
I think I found the police informants.
Their behavior is really suspicious.

519
00:44:51,880 --> 00:44:54,240
MUEANGPHRAI BAND

520
00:45:09,360 --> 00:45:10,840
This is my house.

521
00:45:14,320 --> 00:45:16,120
It doesn't look like anyone's home.

522
00:45:18,800 --> 00:45:20,280
Uncle Tharin is here.

523
00:45:20,360 --> 00:45:22,280
Where? Let's go.

524
00:45:34,840 --> 00:45:36,080
Where have you been?

525
00:45:38,320 --> 00:45:41,120
Well, last night…

526
00:45:41,200 --> 00:45:42,640
You ran off to sing.

527
00:45:45,320 --> 00:45:46,800
Then there was a shooting

528
00:45:48,320 --> 00:45:49,160
and bombs thrown.

529
00:45:50,960 --> 00:45:53,120
Something this serious happened.

530
00:45:54,280 --> 00:45:55,880
And when I called, you wouldn't answer.

531
00:45:57,840 --> 00:45:59,240
Why are you acting like this, Poona?

532
00:46:02,080 --> 00:46:03,040
Well, I…

533
00:46:04,600 --> 00:46:08,360
Poona was injured,
so I took her to rest at my house.

534
00:46:09,000 --> 00:46:11,800
My name is Mueangphrai.
I'm the band leader.

535
00:46:41,360 --> 00:46:42,840
Louder!

536
00:46:55,880 --> 00:46:59,080
Last night, I was worried sick.
Why didn't you ask me to pick you up?

537
00:46:59,160 --> 00:47:02,040
I didn't want to trouble you, Uncle.
It was already late.

538
00:47:02,120 --> 00:47:05,560
You won't trouble me,
but you'll trouble others?

539
00:47:05,640 --> 00:47:08,760
Going to someone else's house like this,
do you think that's right?

540
00:47:11,840 --> 00:47:15,080
Please don't blame her.
I was more than willing

541
00:47:15,160 --> 00:47:17,960
to take care of her myself.

542
00:47:21,040 --> 00:47:22,280
And who are you?

543
00:48:02,200 --> 00:48:03,560
I'm Tharin.

544
00:48:03,640 --> 00:48:05,040
NEXT EPISODE

545
00:48:05,120 --> 00:48:06,480
I'm not Phupha.

546
00:48:07,400 --> 00:48:12,280
If you keep expecting me to be him,
we'll never be able to talk.

547
00:48:12,360 --> 00:48:15,320
It's time we got our revenge.

548
00:48:15,400 --> 00:48:20,280
<i>If you won't do it for yourself,</i>
<i>at least do it for Poona.</i>

549
00:48:20,800 --> 00:48:23,760
Let me be the one
to steal that teddy bear.

550
00:48:27,000 --> 00:48:30,680
Just wait for the competition.
I'm going to beat you for sure.

551
00:48:30,760 --> 00:48:33,120
- You're amazing!
- Yeah.

552
00:48:33,200 --> 00:48:34,120
Hey!

553
00:48:34,880 --> 00:48:35,880
Who are you two?

554
00:48:36,960 --> 00:48:38,080
Down!

555
00:51:33,120 --> 00:51:37,120
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
